"Binder D., Brückl E., Roch K.H., Behm M., Schöner W., Hynek B.","Determination of total ice volume and ice-thickness distribution of two glaciers in the Hohe Tauern region, Eastern Alps, from GPR data",2009,"Annals of Glaciology","50","51",,"71","79",,,10.3189/172756409789097522,"http://www.scopus.com/inward/record.url?eid=2-s2.0-65349133286&partnerID=40&md5=68a48961e69fb056d2848391bd5482d3","Institute of Geodesy and Geophysics, Vienna University of Technology, Gusshausstrasse 27-29/128, A-1040 Vienna, Austria; Central Institute for Meteorology and Geodynamics (ZAMG), Hohe Warte 38, A-1190 Vienna, Austria","Binder, D., Institute of Geodesy and Geophysics, Vienna University of Technology, Gusshausstrasse 27-29/128, A-1040 Vienna, Austria; Brückl, E., Institute of Geodesy and Geophysics, Vienna University of Technology, Gusshausstrasse 27-29/128, A-1040 Vienna, Austria; Roch, K.H., Institute of Geodesy and Geophysics, Vienna University of Technology, Gusshausstrasse 27-29/128, A-1040 Vienna, Austria; Behm, M., Institute of Geodesy and Geophysics, Vienna University of Technology, Gusshausstrasse 27-29/128, A-1040 Vienna, Austria; Schöner, W., Central Institute for Meteorology and Geodynamics (ZAMG), Hohe Warte 38, A-1190 Vienna, Austria; Hynek, B., Central Institute for Meteorology and Geodynamics (ZAMG), Hohe Warte 38, A-1190 Vienna, Austria","Global warming is causing an apparent rapid retreat of many glaciers worldwide. In addition to mass-balance investigation, the determination and monitoring of total glacial ice volume and ice-thickness distribution are important parameters for understanding the interactions between climate and the complex glacier system. Because of spatially irregular and sparse datasets, scaling of volume and ice-thickness distribution is often a challenging problem. This study focuses on two small (&lt;2km2) temperate glaciers in the Hohe Tauern (Eastern Alps) region of central Austria. The period 2003-04 saw the first use of ground-penetrating radar (GPR) to determine the total ice volume and ice-thickness distribution of the two glaciers. A centre frequency of 20MHz was used in point measuring mode. Despite variable data quality, bedrock reflections up to depths of &gt;100 m were identified in the data. The acquired GPR data are irregularly distributed and the spatial density is too low to calculate reasonable bedrock topography with standard interpolation approaches. Thus one main focus of this study was to develop an appropriate interpolation technique. Eventually, kriging technique and a glacial mechanically based interpolation parameter were used. Mean calculated ice thicknesses for the two investigated glaciers are 40-50 m, with a maximum of 150-165 m. No direct validation data are available, so different considerations support the computed bedrock topography.",,"glacier; ground penetrating radar; ice thickness; interpolation; kriging; mass balance; spatial distribution; Alps; Austria; Central Europe; Eastern Alps; Eurasia; Europe; Hohe Tauern",,,,,,"Arie, K., Brückl, E., Eisdickenmessungen auf gletschern der ostalpen (2001) Zentralanstalt für Meteorologie und Geodynamik 1851-2001: 150 Jahre Meteorologie und Geophysik in Österreich, pp. 768-780. , Hammerl, C., W. Lenhardt, R. Steinacker and P. Steinhaus, eds. Graz, Leykam; Auer, I., Böhm, R., Schöner, W., Leymüller, M., Das klima des sonnblicks: Klimaatlas und klimatographie der gawstation sonnblick einschließlich der umgebenden gebirgsregion. Österreich (2002) Beitr. Meteorol. Geophys., p. 28; Bahr, D.B., Width and length scaling of glaciers (1997) J. Glaciol., 43 (145), pp. 557-562; Bahr, D.B., Meier, M.F., Peckham, S.D., The physical basis of glacier volume-area scaling (1997) J. Geophys. Res., 102 (B9), pp. 20355-20362; Bamber, J.L., Layberry, R.L., Gogineni, S.P., A new ice thickness and bed dataset for the Greenland ice sheet. 1. Measurement, data reduction, and errors (2001) J. Ceophys. Res., 106 (D24), pp. 33773-33780; Banks, M.E., Pelletier, J.D., Forward modeling of ice topography on Mars to infer basal shear stress conditions (2008) J. Geophys. Res., 113 (E1), pp. E01001. , 10.1029/2007JE002895; Bindschadler, R., A numerical model of temperate glacier flow applied to the quiescent phase of a surge-type glacier (1982) J. Glaciol., 28 (99), pp. 239-265; Blindow, N., Thyssen, F., Ice thickness and inner structure of the Vernagtferner (Ötztal Alps): Results of electromagnetic reflection measurements (1986) Z Gletscherkd. Glazialgeol., 22 (1), pp. 43-60; Brückl, E., Eine methode zur volumenbestimmung von gletschern auf grund der plastizitätstheorie (1970) Arch. Meteorol. Geophys. Bioklimatol., Ser. A., 19, pp. 317-328; Fountain, A.G., Jacobel, R.W., Advances in ice radar studies of a temperate alpine glacier, South Cascade Glacier, Washington, U.S.A (1997) Annals of Glaciology, 24, pp. 303-308; Frolov, A.D., Macheret, Y.Y., On dielectric properties of dry and wet snow (1999) Hydrol. Process., 13 (12-13), pp. 1755-1760; Greuell, W., Hintereisferner, Austria: Mass-balance reconstruction and numerical modelling of the historical length variations (1992) Journal of Glaciology, 38 (129), pp. 233-244; Gross, G., Der flächenverlust der gletscher in österreich 1850-1920-1969 (1987) Z Gletscherkd. Glazialgeol., 23 (2), pp. 131-141; Gudmundsson, G.H., A three-dimensional numerical model of the confluence area of Unteraargletscher, Bernese Alps, Switzerland (1999) J. Glaciol., 45 (150), pp. 219-230; Haeberli, W., Schweizer, J., Rhonegletscher 1850: Eismechanische überlegungen zu einem historischen gletscherstand (1988) ETH-Zürich VAWE Mitt, 94, pp. 59-70; Haeberli, W., Wächter, H.P., Schmid, W., Sidler, C., Erste erfahrungen mit dem u.s.-geological-survey-monopuls-radioecholot im firn, eis und permafrost der schweizer alpen (1983) Z Gletscherkd. Glazialgeol., 19 (1), pp. 61-72; Herzfeld, U.C., Eriksson, M.G., Holmlund, P., On the influence of kriging parameters on the cartographic output - A study in mapping sub